On 6/10/11 11:36 AM, courtney hook wrote:
> I'm going to be looking for a spare alt. for my "travel parts" for the summer trips. My 70amp starter is looking like it's made from unobtanium these days, so figured I'd grab a 55amp one off the samba. I need to know what else has to be changed out to use the 55amp when that time comes re: grommets, etc?


You'll need the cooling boot that hooks to the fan shroud.  You'll need 
the backing plate that covers the end of the alternator.  You'll need a 
pulley.

